President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania in response to the conditions caused by Hurricane Irene. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Ed Smith has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.